cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for learning selectional preferences for classes of verbs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also presents a statistical model for learning these preferences, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses a small sense-disambiguated corpus, which involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) and the model can be used for word sense disambiguation (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the relationship between different classes of verbs, which can be seen as a network analysis problem (cs.SI).
